<li id="cite_note-Sunstein-24"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Sunstein_24-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Sunstein_24-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Sunstein, Cass R. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.cato.org/pubs/regulation/regv25n4/v25n4-9.pdf">The Paralyzing Principle: Does the Precautionary Principle Point us in any Helpful Direction?</a> Regulation, Winter 2002–2003, The Cato Institute.</span></li>
